│ isn't formed, so the assert aborts. A robust fix is to gracefully handle the absence of EPResumeVal by falling back to using the vector trip count (EPI.VectorTripCount) as the resume   │
│ start for the canonical IV. This maintains correctness—the epilogue IV should start at the number of iterations processed by the main vector loop—and avoids the hard assert. I will     │
│ modify preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop to use EPI.VectorTripCount when EPResumeVal isn't found.                                                                                         │
